---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Brian Baldock. Identity, security, and AI infrastructure, plus the line-cook habits that still run the workshop.">
  <article class="container about">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <img
      class="portrait"
      src="/images/about/brian-portrait.jpg"
      width="170"
      height="170"
      alt="Brian Baldock, bearded and wearing glasses and a dark blazer, smiling with arms crossed."
      loading="eager"
      decoding="async"
    />

    <p>
      I'm Brian Baldock. I work on identity, security, and AI infrastructure.
      The unglamorous plumbing that decides whether everything else holds up.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before tech, I worked the line in restaurant kitchens. That isn't a
      fun-fact footnote. The habits I built there (work clean, prep before
      you're slammed, call out problems before they hit the pass) are the same
      ones I lean on now when I'm hardening a tenant or chasing a tunnel that
      won't come up at 1am. There's always something to clean.
    </p>
    <p>
      I publish what I learn here, usually after a deployment, sometimes after
      a mistake. The mistakes tend to make the better posts.
    </p>
    <p>
      The alligator-with-a-taco mascot is a long story. The short version: it
      stuck.
    </p>

    <h2>Certifications</h2>
    <p class="muted">The credentials I actually use, grouped by what they're for.</p>

    <h3>Security and identity</h3>
    <ul class="certs">
      <li>Microsoft Certified: Cybersecurity Architect Expert (SC-100)</li>
      <li>Microsoft Certified: Security Operations Analyst Associate (SC-200)</li>
      <li>Microsoft Certified: Identity and Access Administrator Associate (SC-300)</li>
      <li>ISC2 Certified in Cybersecurity (CC)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Applied Skills (hands-on, scenario-based)</h3>
    <ul class="certs">
      <li>Defend against cyberthreats with Microsoft Defender XDR</li>
      <li>Implement information protection and data loss prevention with Microsoft Purview</li>
      <li>Prepare security and compliance for Microsoft 365 Copilot</li>
      <li>Administer Active Directory Domain Services</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Breadth and leadership</h3>
    <ul class="certs">
      <li>Microsoft 365 Certified: Administrator Expert</li>
      <li>Microsoft Certified Trainer (MCT) 2026</li>
      <li>VMware Certified Professional: Data Center Virtualization</li>
      <li>Prosci Certified Change Practitioner</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="verify">
      See the full badge wall on
      <a href="https://www.credly.com/users/brian-baldock">Credly</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Find me elsewhere</h2>
    <ul class="elsewhere">
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/brianbaldock/">LinkedIn</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/brianbaldock">GitHub</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/brianbaldock.net">Bluesky</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>About this site</h2>
    <p>
      This blog runs on <a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a>, lives in
      <a href="https://github.com/brianbaldock/blog">a public GitHub repo</a>,
      and ships through GitHub Pages. Words are
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC&nbsp;BY&nbsp;4.0</a>;
      code snippets are MIT.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: right;
    width: 170px;
    height: 170px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1rem 1.75rem;
    border: 3px solid var(--accent);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }
  .about h3 {
    margin-top: 1.4em;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  ul.certs {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5em 0 0;
  }
  ul.certs li {
    padding: 0.4em 0 0.4em 1.5em;
    position: relative;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  ul.certs li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  ul.certs li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.95em;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: var(--accent);
  }
  .verify {
    margin-top: 1em;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }
  ul.elsewhere {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .portrait {
      float: none;
      display: block;
      margin: 0 auto 1.25rem;
      width: 140px;
      height: 140px;
    }
  }
</style>
